# CLAUDE.md — agent-track integration

<!-- Copy the section below into your project's CLAUDE.md -->

## Agent Protocol

This project uses `.track` for multi-agent coordination. Your session is **automatically tracked** via hooks — no registration, heartbeats, or deregistration needed.

### Before starting work

Check the board and available tickets:
```bash
track board --last 10
track list
```

### Creating and claiming tickets

Create a ticket — it's **auto-claimed** to you:
```bash
track create --title "Fix auth token refresh" --desc "See docs/phase2-plan.md:45-72"
```

To create a ticket for another agent to pick up:
```bash
track create --title "Add retry logic" --no-claim
```

To claim an existing unclaimed ticket:
```bash
track claim T-NNNN
```

### While working

- **Reference ticket IDs in git commits**: `T-0001: fix token refresh logic`
- **Check the board** if you need context from other agents: `track board --last 10`
- **Post to the board** for questions or blockers:
  ```bash
  track board -m "Need help with auth module" --ticket T-NNNN
  ```

Everything else is tracked automatically:
- File changes, test runs, commands — captured via hooks
- File conflicts with other agents — detected automatically
- Heartbeats — every tool call is an implicit heartbeat

### When done

```bash
track update T-NNNN --status review
```

### Rules

- **One ticket at a time.** Finish or release before claiming another.
- **Check the board first.** Another agent may already be working on what you need.
- **Reference ticket IDs in commits** so progress is trackable.
- **Never modify `.track/` files directly.** Always use the `track` CLI.
